We apply our previously developed [44, 45] radial atomic reactivity descriptors for the HBA and HBD sites, encoding the electronic and steric environment of an atom, together with Gaussian Process Regression (GPR) [81]. It provides a native estimate of the variance by taking into account the distance of the query to the training data in descriptor space. We used the GPR implementation of scikit-learn 0.19.1 [82] with a combined kernel function:1K=C∗M+W,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
